      Alan F
      Westfield, Massachusetts
      1293628
      Reviewed May 25, 2019
      France Exemplified

      A fisherman might dream of finding the ideal fishing spot. While we have been to many Michelin 1, 2 and a few 3 star restaurants, our ideal find is a bistro/brasserie/bouchon where the staff enjoys each other and their customers, where the cooking is first rate and has been pleasing their regulars for generations, and where we would be delighted to return to again and again. Le Galopin is that kind of place. The silverware sparkles, the bright red banquettes are festive and the atmosphere reflects lots of people having a very good time.

      Nearly 5 weeks into this trip, this is one of just a few restaurants we will remember with both precision and great pleasure. The wait staff is kind, truly professional and graceful in their rounds.

      Our Cancale oyster starter was the best of this trip. The wild shrimp and pasta main was delicious. The blackboard notice of a Brillat Savarin with truffles and an aged, 30 month Comte' couldn't be ignored, and the cheese course was optimal. Desserts too were delicious. A crisp Chablis added to our enjoyment. All of the above at a fair price.

      We will be remembering Le Galopin for a long time and know we will be welcomed when we return.

      petero251966
      Garmisch-Partenkirchen, Germany
      41347
      Reviewed November 6, 2018 via mobile
      More than expected

      When I first entered I thought just another typical French Brasserie but already a look at the menu did not disappoint. Lots of fish and sea food and not a lot of the standard dishes, but some creative compositions such as my starter of crab meat, salmon and scallop tartare with Yuzu sauce. My main dish was slightly disappointing as the wagyu beef tasted more like liver a d the croquettes were too fluffy and not very tasty. The portions are good and the service excellent. As the others enjoyed their respective meals ( monk fish or sole as well as Riz de veau) still a narrow 5 star for me given also the sensibly priced menu options.
